miles up the trail,

00:04:00.260 --> 00:04:01.290
and at the far end of the meadow

00:04:01.290 --> 00:04:04.480
about 80 yards is a grizzly bear sow.

00:04:04.480 --> 00:04:05.313
- Hello.

00:04:05.313 --> 00:04:07.630
(girls gasp)

00:04:07.630 --> 00:04:08.483
- With two cubs.

00:04:08.483 --> 00:04:09.650
- [Girls] Aww.

00:04:11.980 --> 00:04:13.810
- [Daniel] Female grizzly
bear is called a sow?

00:04:13.810 --> 00:04:14.990
- [Todd] Sow, yes.

00:04:14.990 --> 00:04:17.510
- Now how do you know that it's not like

00:04:17.510 --> 00:04:19.950
a single father raising his kid.

00:04:19.950 --> 00:04:21.330
- [Todd] Fathers do not raise the cubs,

00:04:21.330 --> 00:04:22.880
it's always with the sows.

00:04:22.880 --> 00:04:25.770
- You think with the current
#MeToo movement and everything

00:04:25.770 --> 00:04:26.830
that maybe the fathers

00:04:26.830 --> 00:04:27.663
would step up.
- Something should change

00:04:27.663 --> 00:04:28.496
there maybe, yeah.

00:04:28.496 --> 00:04:30.130
- But no, huh interesting.

00:04:30.130 --> 00:04:32.290
- She runs over the ridge, disappears.

00:04:32.290 --> 00:04:34.040
I thought, alright she's gone that way,

00:04:34.040 --> 00:04:35.960
I'll go up the trail and continue my day

00:04:35.960 --> 00:04:37.370
I'll never see her again.

00:04:37.370 --> 00:04:39.820
I took a few steps, heard a noise,

00:04:39.820 --> 00:04:41.980
and she had circled around the ridge

00:04:41.980 --> 00:04:43.599
and came in behind me charging.

00:04:43.599 --> 00:04:45.766
(roaring)

00:04:46.620 --> 00:04:47.453
- [Daniel] Like how long of a time--

00:04:47.453 --> 00:04:48.380
